def: A gaping after; eager desire; craving. [R.] Bp. Hall.
A field. [Obs.] Spelman. "Woods and wonges." Havelok the Dane.
One who suborns or procures another to take, a false oath; onewho procures another to do a bad action.
An inking pad used in lithographic printing.
A minute and tedious discourse on trifling things.
A little lock of hair, plastered in a spiral form on the templeor forehead with spittle, or other adhesive substance. [Colloq.]
Office or duty of an advocate.
The act of pulling to pieces, or of separating the parts. Bp.Hall.
To intimidate; to restrain or coerce by intimidation orviolence; -- used originally of the intimidation of negro voters, inLouisiana. [Slang, U.S.]
